Text.Value: I have seen a red dragon, flying above the Risen Road.
We must scout the roads and scan the skies for children of Gith. They will lead us to a crèche. There, we will be purified.
I welcome our alliance, kin. We will seek out a crèche.
All right - you are welcome to join me.
All right, we journey together. Let's find this crèche.
Consider your hunger. Fresh blood flows beneath that skin...
A red dragon? Then githyanki are near! Onward - purification awaits us.
When infected with a ghaik tadpole, we must report to a ghustil for purification.
*You also feel answers. She knows more about your condition.*
Join me, then. But I'll be watching you closely.
Half-elf. I suppose the finer details are lost on a creature like you.
Fool. No point in showing a mad dog kindness - it'll still bite you in the end.
Lunge for her neck.
Purificiation it is, then. You and I better find this crèche.
If you wish to be rid of the tadpole, you must either be purified - or beheaded.
Onward, then - purification awaits us.
Fine - we can try working together.
Such tiring mediocrity.
There, we will be purified.
You angered a kith'rak? You are lucky your heart still beats.
The Blade of Frontiers has come to your aid. May I suggest a hearty 'thank you'?
I just resurrected you. May I suggest a hearty 'thank you'?
Come - our search begins. We've no time to waste.
Then we mustn't delay. Onward - purification awaits us.
Wait at my camp. We can speak there.
You will join me. Together, we must find a crèche: our people possess the cure for this infection.
Together, we must find a crèche: my people possess the cure for this infection.
Sigh. I must decline.
I'll trust your judgement - but I won't trust her. Not until I've gotten the measure of her.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Sh addresses the player. She glances at Lae'zel on 'this one'
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This node if SH is available and has approval of the player that's greater than 0

Text.Value: Githyanki attacked me on the Risen Road. They did not survive.
We'll go our separate ways, I think.
A kith'rak accosted me on the Risen Road, but I convinced him to let me live.
Githyanki confronted me on the Risen Road, but I convinced them to let me live.
A slate? A map to the nearest crèche, perhaps.
Enough. A crèche is near - we must seek signs of it. Forward, through the pass.

EditorData.logicalname: At Chokepoint - no map - SH spoke

Text.Value: A crèche is near - we must seek signs of it. Only there can we be purified.
A weapon? Is this what the kith'raki sought from the nautiloid?
I have located the crèche. It lies just beyond the mountain pass.
Shka'keth!

EditorData.NodeContext: SHKA-keth! Just like it is spelled.

Text.Value: They attacked their own kin? This is most extraordinary.
I will await word at your camp. And beware the skies. We are watched.
A crèche is near - we must seek signs of it. Forward, through the pass.
The crèche holds the zaith'isk. It will cleanse us of the parasite.
Very well. But heed my words.
Lies. Just get rid of her.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tersely murmured advice. You're not going to trust her, are you?

Text.Value: You have made an ally from Crèche K'liir - few know such fortune. Call me Lae'zel.
A crèche? Do you mean a hatchery?
And what exactly is a crèche...?
Githyanki protocol is clear: when infected with a ghaik tadpole, we must report to a ghustil for purification.
You were on the gh'ath. The nautiloid. You carry a tadpole.
The cure I offer will suffice as thanks.
Scowl all you like - you have my answer.
You've a sharp tongue, elf. Would that your mind proved its equal.
Leave.
Chk.
Our paths cross again, kin. I might call it fate, if I believed in it.
Our paths cross again, istik. I might call it fate, if I believed in it.
Then we know our destination. Onward.
We seem like a poor match, frankly. Let's go our separate ways.
Neither the ghaik nor the crash have broken your spirit. Yes - you may still be of considerable use.
Bah. A cure must be our chief concern. Onward - purification awaits us.
I'm dreadfully curious: might one neutralise the tadpole while keeping its powers?
And beware the skies. We are watched.
Search these corpses for a map, and beware the skies. We are watched.
Well?
Has the error of your ways become clear?
Yes - I must read it at once. Purification may be at hand!
I will await word at your camp.
Locating a crèche would be wise indeed. Where might we find one?
Wait at my camp. We can speak there.
I know my teachings. There are no half measures.
I do not yet know - we will seek it together. Protocol is clear:
You angered githyanki? You are lucky your heart still beats.
I have seen githyanki, near the mountain pass. One rode a red dragon.
You would sacrifice yourself to ghaik?
A kith'rak attacked me on the Risen Road. He sought a weapon of some sort.
Githyanki attacked me on the Risen Road. They sought a weapon of some sort.
I would like you to join me.
I'm told of githyanki near a mountain pass, off the Risen Road.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Set from talking to Zorru or to the dead tiefling at the 3 ogres

Text.Value: Careful - she obviously sees your kindness as weakness. Don't let her take advantage.

EditorData.NodeContext: Speaking to the player regarding Lae'zel. Discreetly urging caution

Text.Value: A crèche is near - we must seek signs of it. Search these corpses for a map.
You survived an encounter with githyanki? Extraordinary. They must have suffered prior injury...
I don't know this protocol. What does purification entail?
Enough. A crèche is near - we must seek signs of it. Search these corpses for a map.

EditorData.logicalname: At Chkpnt. - map available, SH spoke

Text.Value: I have discovered a githyanki slate. Perhaps you can read it.
By Vlaakith's covenant, I know little more.
By covenant, I can say no more.
The longer the parasite lives, the more of us it consumes.
You may as well suggest a wyvern bow to worms.
Leave.
I live. Vlaakith blesses me once more!
We must set out for a crèche - purification awaits.
I will be at your camp. Do not keep me waiting.
It is many things. A hatchery, a training grounds, a shelter.
*Your skull briefly aches, and you are her. You feel the woman's momentary relief over her revival - and her loathing of the parasite lodged in her brain.*
We scout the roads and scan the skies for children of Gith. They will lead us to a crèche.
I honour our alliance, kin. Let us seek a crèche.
You do not have the authority. Defer to your leader.
You are full up. Dismiss your weakest warrior.

Synopsis:
Lae'zel died in the tutorial. Her body was found on the beach (remember that bodies can be moved though). Player revived her.
The flag ORI_LaezelRecruitment_State_CrashVersionInitiated is set upon loading WLD_Main_A, when this version of the recruitment is activated.
